    <etym xml:lang="ru">Может быть, из %i*kur-ta-%i или %i*kur-tar-%i, nomen agentis от %i*kur-%i
        ‘топить’, ‘ калить’ и пр. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><lang/><w>kūdayati</w><gloss><q>палит</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>жжет</q></gloss><note type="comment" xml:lang="">
                ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="xcl"><lang/><w>kʼrakʼ</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note
                type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><gloss><q>огонь</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Hübschmann._Arm._Gr."
            /><biblScope>462</biblScope></bibl>),[[<mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><lang/><w>küra</w><gloss><q>кузнечный горн</q></gloss></mentioned> относится,
        вероятно, сюда же, и его вряд ли основательно связывать с арабским (будто бы от араб.
        %ikawr-%i ‘скручивать’!); скорее арабское из персидского. Арм. %ik'rak'%i может быть
        заимствованием из ср.иран. %i*kurak%i.]] <mentioned xml:lang="cu"
            ><lang/><w>курити</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
            ><lang/><w>курить</w></mentioned> (для семантики ср. %iвинокур%i, %iкурная изба%i ‘изба
        с открытым очагом’, %iкурень%i ‘место выжига угля’ и др.), <mentioned xml:lang="sl"
                ><lang/><w>kuriti</w><gloss><q>разжигать огонь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="lt"><lang/><w>kurti</w><gloss><q>топить</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="lt"><w/><gloss><q>разжигать огонь</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="got"><lang/><w>hauri</w><gloss><q>уголь</q></gloss></mentioned>.
        Восстанавливать следует и.е. %i*keur-%i, %i*kur-%i, а не %i*ker%i, вопреки <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Pokorny"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">(571 сл.)</biblScope><biblScope
                xml:lang="en">(571 ff.)</biblScope></bibl>. — Сюда же, вероятно, <mentioned
            xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>кръчии</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="orv"
                ><lang/><w>корчий</w><gloss><q>кузнец</q></gloss></mentioned> (отсюда %iКорчев%i
        древнерусское название города Керчи, буквально „Кузнецк“); %i*кърч-%i из %i*kur-tyo-%i?
        Связь c <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>kar-</w><gloss><q>делать</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Fick"/><biblScope>I 24, 384</biblScope></bibl>. —
                <bibl><ref target="#ref_Berneker"/><biblScope>671</biblScope></bibl>) менее
        правдоподобна. — Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_K0yrdalægon"/>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It may be from %i*kur-ta-%i or %i*kur-tar-%i, nomen agentis from %i*kur-%i
        ‘stoke’, ‘heat’ etc. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>kūdayati</w><gloss><q>is
                    burning</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
                ><lang/><w>kʼrakʼ</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment"
                xml:lang=""> ()</note><gloss><q>fire</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Hübschmann._Arm._Gr."/><biblScope>462</biblScope></bibl>),[[<mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>küra</w><gloss><q>forge</q></gloss></mentioned> is probably
        related to it as well, and it should not be related to Arabic (as if from Arabic %ikawr-%i
        ‘twist’!); it is more probable that the Arabic word is from Persian. Armenian %ik'rak'%i may
        have been borrowed from Middle Iranian %i*kurak%i.]] <mentioned xml:lang="cu"
                ><lang/><w>курити</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
            ><lang/><w>курить</w></mentioned> (for the semantics cf. %iвинокур%i, %iкурная изба%i
        ‘hut heated by a chimneyless stove’, %iкурень%i ‘coal burning place’ etc.), <mentioned
            xml:lang="sl"><lang/><w>kuriti</w><gloss><q>light the fire</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="lt"
            ><lang/><w>kurti</w><gloss><q>stoke</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="lt"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>light the fire</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="got"><lang/><w>hauri</w><gloss><q>coal</q></gloss></mentioned>. The
        Indo-European forms %i*keur-%i, %i*kur-%i should be reconstructed, not %i*ker%i, contrary to
                <bibl><ref target="#ref_Pokorny"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">(571
                сл.)</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">(571 ff.)</biblScope></bibl>. — The
        following words are related to it as well: <mentioned xml:lang="cu"
            ><lang/><w>кръчии</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="orv"
                    ><lang/><w>корчий</w><gloss><q>blacksmith</q></gloss></mentioned> (Old Russian
        name for the Kerch city %iКорчев%i is from it,literally “blacksmith town“); is %i*кърч-%i
        from %i*kur-tyo-%i? The relation to <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><lang/><w>kar-</w><gloss><q>do</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Fick"/><biblScope>I 24, 384</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Berneker"/><biblScope>671</biblScope></bibl>) is less plausible. — Cf.
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_K0yrdalægon"/>.</etym>
</entry>
